lse},{"id":43896,"name":"ToolmakerSteve","username":"ToolmakerSteve","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/t/ba9def/{size}.png","created_at":"2021-12-03T21:17:37.629Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eThank you elix. I’m seeing visual artifacts using these parallax shaders.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOcclusion: thin “contour lines” visible - is this expected? fixable?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/mCDXedHcCh8GaQQZIH8H7KRTjf7.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"occlusion parallax - thin contour lines visible\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d_2_526x500.jpeg\" alt=\"occlusion parallax - thin contour lines visible\" data-base62-sha1=\"mCDXedHcCh8GaQQZIH8H7KRTjf7\" width=\"526\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d_2_526x500.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eocclusion parallax - thin contour lines visible\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e605×575 84.2 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOffset: no depth at all, instead, textures distort:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/nzqZsuZ1xFNM2Ld6jV6C0xD8LNX.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"offset parallax - distorted texture\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5_2_645x499.jpeg\" alt=\"offset parallax - distorted texture\" data-base62-sha1=\"nzqZsuZ1xFNM2Ld6jV6C0xD8LNX\" width=\"645\" height=\"499\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5_2_645x499.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eoffset parallax - distorted texture\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e898×696 200 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is on standard Box model. Same behavior if apply to my wall. It also happens using the various offset/occlusion materials and textures provided in that repo.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWindows 10, OpenGL, \u003ca href=\"http://Urho.Net\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eUrho.Net\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn case it was something else in that scene, I’ve also tested in a simple scene, with nothing but a ground plane and some Boxes, a simple directional light, no shadows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIf approach any of 6 faces of box straight on, the texture looks perfect. As increase camera angle relative to plane of the surface, those distortions appear/increase.\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":6,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2021-12-03T21:31:08.550Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":5,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":16,"readers_count":15,"score":13.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":7071,"topic_slug":"is-there-a-technique-that-supports-surface-displacement","display_username":"ToolmakerSteve","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"http://Urho.Net","internal":false,"reflection":false,"clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/a/a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"a53370844f78a17c9989098e654eeb137cdaace5.jpeg","clicks":0},{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/9/9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d.jpeg","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"9e8e219f309fa80f84625e16b440e5681623780d.jpeg","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"username":"elix22","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/elix22/{size}/1437_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summ